ironmental destruction during armed conflict constitutes a \\\"Class A\\\" war crime, equivalent to direct attacks on civilian populations. The ruling follows a three-year investigation into the deliberate flooding of the Marand Valley during the border conflicts of 2019. The court\\u2019s presiding judge, Justice Althea Moretti, stated that the intentional destruction of life-sustaining ecosystems is a violation of the fundamental right to survival. \\\"The weaponization of the environment leaves scars that last for generations, and those who authorize such tactics must be held to account under the same statutes as other genocidal acts,\\\" Moretti read from the bench in The Hague. The court issued arrest warrants for four former military commanders and two sitting cabinet ministers from the region, marking the first time the tribunal has targeted high-ranking officials for ecological crimes. Legal scholars suggest the ruling sets a significant precedent that could lead to future prosecutions involving industrial pollution and resource depletion in conflict zones. Several nations have already expressed concern over the ruling, arguing it oversteps the court's jurisdiction and interferes with national sovereignty over natural resources.\",\n          \"The Senate Committee on Commerce, Science, and Transportation voted 14-12 on Tuesday to postpone the confirmation hearing for Arthur Vance, the nominee for Secretary of Commerce, citing unresolved discrepancies in his international financial disclosures. Senator Margaret Thorne (R-OH), chair of the oversight subcommittee, stated that a recent internal audit revealed $42 million in previously unreported offshore holdings linked to a maritime logistics firm based in Singapore. \\\"The integrity of the department relies on full transparency from its leadership, and these omissions present a significant barrier to our vetting process,\\\" Thorne said during the morning session. Vance, who previously served as CEO of Global Trade Ventures, has maintained that the assets were part of a blind trust established in 2018. However, committee analysts argued that the trust's structure allowed for continued managerial influence, violating the Ethics in Government Act. The delay marks the first time in fifteen years that a cabinet nominee has been stalled by a committee vote prior to a formal floor hearing. Democratic leaders expressed frustration, with Senator Julian Pierce calling the move a \\\"partisan tactic\\\" designed to slow the administration's economic agenda. The committee is expected to reconvene on the matter following a 30-day review period by the Office of Government Ethics.\"\n        ],\n        \"semantic_type\": \"\",\n        \"description\": \"\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"column\": \"Truth\",\n      \"properties\": {\n        \"dtype\": \"number\",\n        \"std\": 0,\n        \"min\": 0,\n        \"max\": 0,\n        \"num_unique_values\": 1,\n        \"samples\": [\n          0\n        ],\n        \"semantic_type\": \"\",\n        \"description\": \"\"\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}"}},"metadata":{}}]},{"cell_type":"code","metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"34f846c8","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1773526671511,"user_tz":240,"elapsed":11,"user":{"displayName":"Yiwei Wang","userId":"13953772695009695674"}},"outputId":"a2123c3a-eb63-4304-f586-5f74644f825a"},"source":["# Update TRUTH_COL for the new dataset 'Expanded Dataset.xlsx'\n","# Assuming the 'Truth' column was correctly named when loaded.\n","TRUTH_COL = \"Truth\"\n","TEXT_COL = \"text\"\n","ID_COL = \"row_id\"\n","\n","# Ensure an ID column exists for checkpointing\n","if ID_COL not in df.columns:\n","    print(f\"Adding '{ID_COL}' to the DataFrame for checkpointing.\")\n","    df[ID_COL] = df.apply(make_stable_row_id, axis=1)\n","\n","print(f\"Updated TRUTH_COL to: {TRUTH_COL}\")\n","print(f\"Updated TEXT_COL to: {TEXT_COL}\")"],"execution_count":null,"outputs":[{"outpu